    "mimeType": "text/markdown",
    "content": "# tn-avatar Avatar\n\n---\ncategory: display\ntitle: Avatar / 头像\ncomponent-dir: avatar\nprimary-tags:\n  - tn-avatar\nrelated-tags:\n  - tn-avatar-group\nstatus: stable\nsource-dir: node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/avatar\nstyle-source:\n  - node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/avatar.scss\n  - node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/avatar-group.scss\ndemo-pages:\n  - src/demo-pages/basic/avatar/index.vue\n---\n\n## Component Role\n\n`avatar` is the user or entity portrait component, and `avatar-group` arranges\nmultiple avatars into an overlapped group.\n\n## Best Fit Scenarios\n\n- user profile or participant display\n- message lists and social cards\n- stacked participant previews\n- small visual identity chips with icons, letters, or images\n\n## Avoid Using It For\n\n- decorative standalone images with no identity meaning\n- large gallery-style media layouts\n- badges or tags that only carry small status text\n\n## Recommended Repo Usage\n\n```vue\n<tn-avatar url=\"https://example.com/avatar.png\" />\n```\n\nUse `tn-avatar-group` when the page shows a small set of related participants.\n\n## Family Structure\n\n- parent tag: `tn-avatar-group`\n- child tag: `tn-avatar`\n- grouped overlap, border color, and spacing are managed by the group\n- each avatar still controls its own image, icon, text fallback, and badge\n\n## Key Capabilities\n\n### Avatar Variants\n\n- image via `url`\n- icon avatar\n- text avatar\n- themed `type` colors\n- `shape=\"square\"` and default rounded shape\n\n### Decoration And Layout\n\n- size presets and custom numeric size\n- `bg-color`\n- `icon-config`\n- `border` and `border-color`\n- `shadow` and `shadow-color`\n- badge and badge-config on single avatars\n- group `gap` and group `border-color`\n\n## Boundary With Similar Components\n\n- use `avatar` for identity display, not general image media\n- use `badge` beside or on an avatar for counts or status dots when identity\n  and status are separate concerns\n- use `photo-album` when the content is a gallery rather than a profile marker\n\n## AI Usage Notes\n\n- pick image, icon, or text fallback intentionally based on data availability\n- keep avatar sizing consistent inside the same list or card\n- use `avatar-group` only for small participant summaries, not full rosters\n- verify full badge config and overlap rules from source before abstracting a\n  reusable team-member component\n\n## Related Demos\n\n- `src/demo-pages/basic/avatar/index.vue`\n\n## Drill-Down Paths\n\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/avatar/src/avatar.vue`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/avatar/src/avatar.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/avatar/src/avatar-group.vue`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/avatar/src/avatar-group.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/avatar.scss`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/avatar-group.scss`\n\n## Evidence Status\n\n- Demo confirmed:\n  - `src/demo-pages/basic/avatar/index.vue`\n- Source paths mapped:\n  - `components/avatar/src/avatar.vue`\n  - `components/avatar/src/avatar-group.vue`\n- Still verify in source:\n  - full group prop surface and expose API\n  - exact badge behavior when avatars are grouped\n"
