    "uri": "tuniao://tnui/components/badge",
    "name": "badge",
    "description": "tn-badge Badge",
    "mimeType": "text/markdown",
    "content": "# tn-badge Badge\n\n---\ncategory: display\ntitle: Badge / 徽标\ncomponent-dir: badge\nprimary-tags:\n  - tn-badge\nrelated-tags: []\nstatus: stable\nsource-dir: node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/badge\nstyle-source:\n  - node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/badge.scss\ndemo-pages:\n  - src/demo-pages/basic/badge/index.vue\n---\n\n## Component Role\n\n`tn-badge` is a compact marker for counts, dots, icons, and small status labels\nattached to content or shown standalone.\n\n## Best Fit Scenarios\n\n- unread counts\n- small alert markers\n- icon or dot status on cards and tabs\n- attached status markers on avatars or custom blocks\n\n## Avoid Using It For\n\n- long labels or descriptive tags\n- standalone navigation items with large tap targets\n- full content chips where `tag` is more appropriate\n\n## Recommended Repo Usage\n\n```vue\n<tn-badge :value=\"99\">\n  <view class=\"badge-content\" />\n</tn-badge>\n```\n\n## Key Capabilities\n\n### Value Modes\n\n- numeric or string `value`\n- icon value strings\n- `dot` mode\n- `max` for capped count display\n\n### Layout And Style\n\n- can wrap child content or render standalone\n- `type` theme variants\n- size presets and custom numeric size\n- `font-size`\n- `bg-color`\n- `text-color`\n- `absolute`\n- `absolute-center`\n- `absolute-position`\n\n## Boundary With Similar Components\n\n- use `badge` for micro-status and count markers\n- use `tag` for labeled semantic chips\n- use avatar built-in badge support when the badge is tightly coupled to the\n  avatar itself\n\n## AI Usage Notes\n\n- keep badge text very short; counts and icons are the common use case\n- use `dot` when the exact count is not important\n- if the badge anchors to custom content, verify positioning in the page rather\n  than forcing manual offsets first\n- confirm overflow and capping behavior from source when large counts matter\n\n## Related Demos\n\n- `src/demo-pages/basic/badge/index.vue`\n\n## Drill-Down Paths\n\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/badge/src/badge.vue`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/badge/src/badge.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/badge/src/instance.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/badge.scss`\n\n## Evidence Status\n\n- Demo confirmed:\n  - `src/demo-pages/basic/badge/index.vue`\n- Source paths mapped:\n  - `components/badge/src/badge.vue`\n  - `components/badge/src/badge.ts`\n- Still verify in source:\n  - exact count overflow formatting\n  - whether extra slots or expose methods exist\n"
