    "description": "tn-keyboard Keyboard",
    "mimeType": "text/markdown",
    "content": "# tn-keyboard Keyboard\n\n---\ncategory: form\ntitle: Keyboard / 自定义键盘\ncomponent-dir: keyboard\nprimary-tags:\n  - tn-keyboard\nrelated-tags: []\nstatus: stable\nsource-dir: node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/keyboard\nstyle-source:\n  - node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/keyboard.scss\ndemo-pages:\n  - src/demo-pages/component/keyboard/index.vue\n---\n\n## Component Role\n\n`tn-keyboard` is a custom on-screen keyboard for constrained numeric, ID-card,\nand vehicle-plate style input.\n\n## Best Fit Scenarios\n\n- custom payment or verification numeric entry\n- ID card input\n- vehicle plate input\n- cases where the page must avoid the native keyboard and control key layout\n\n## Avoid Using It For\n\n- general text input\n- forms that work well with the system keyboard\n- freeform content editing\n\n## Recommended Repo Usage\n\n```vue\n<tn-keyboard\n  v-model=\"inputValue\"\n  v-model:show=\"openKeyboard\"\n  mode=\"number\"\n/>\n```\n\n## Key Capabilities\n\n### Keyboard Modes\n\n- `number`\n- `digit`\n- `random`\n- `idcard`\n- `car`\n\n### Control Surface\n\n- `v-model` for the input value\n- `v-model:show` for keyboard visibility\n- `mode`\n- `close` event\n\n## Boundary With Similar Components\n\n- use `keyboard` when the key layout must be controlled by the app\n- use `input` with native keyboard when standard text entry is preferable\n- use `number-box` or `slider` when users should adjust a value, not type one\n\n## AI Usage Notes\n\n- pair keyboard visibility with an explicit trigger button or focused field flow\n- keep input reset and close behavior in page logic rather than assuming the\n  keyboard clears automatically\n- choose the mode that matches the domain exactly to prevent invalid input\n- verify delete, confirm, and close event details from source before building a\n  secure-input wrapper\n\n## Related Demos\n\n- `src/demo-pages/component/keyboard/index.vue`\n\n## Drill-Down Paths\n\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/keyboard/src/keyboard.vue`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/keyboard/src/keyboard.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/keyboard/src/instance.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/keyboard.scss`\n\n## Evidence Status\n\n- Demo confirmed:\n  - `src/demo-pages/component/keyboard/index.vue`\n- Source paths mapped:\n  - `components/keyboard/src/keyboard.vue`\n  - `components/keyboard/src/keyboard.ts`\n- Still verify in source:\n  - exact confirm/delete event surface\n  - whether random mode reshuffles every open or only on initialization\n"
