    "content": "# tn-line-progress Line Progress\n\n---\ncategory: display\ntitle: Line Progress / 线性进度条\ncomponent-dir: line-progress\nprimary-tags:\n  - tn-line-progress\nrelated-tags: []\nstatus: stable\nsource-dir: node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/line-progress\nstyle-source:\n  - node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/line-progress.scss\ndemo-pages:\n  - src/demo-pages/component/progress/index.vue\n---\n\n## Component Role\n\n`tn-line-progress` is a horizontal progress display for showing completion\npercentage in a compact bar.\n\n## Best Fit Scenarios\n\n- file or task progress\n- completion summaries inside cards\n- lightweight percentage feedback inside a form or page\n\n## Avoid Using It For\n\n- multi-step workflow progress that should use `steps`\n- loading spinners with no percentage meaning\n- circular or dashboard-style progress visuals\n\n## Recommended Repo Usage\n\n```vue\n<tn-line-progress :percent=\"50\" />\n```\n\n## Key Capabilities\n\n### Progress Display\n\n- `percent`\n- `show-percent`\n- `stripe`\n\n### Visual Controls\n\n- `height`\n- `inactive-color`\n- `active-color`\n\n## Boundary With Similar Components\n\n- use `line-progress` for compact horizontal progress\n- use `circle-progress` for center-focused progress visuals\n- use `loading` when there is no stable percentage value\n\n## AI Usage Notes\n\n- keep percent values normalized to the component’s expected range\n- use `show-percent` when users need explicit numeric confirmation\n- reserve striped style for active/in-motion progress semantics\n- verify animation and percent-clamping behavior in source when values update\n  rapidly\n\n## Related Demos\n\n- `src/demo-pages/component/progress/index.vue`\n\n## Drill-Down Paths\n\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/line-progress/src/line-progress.vue`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/line-progress/src/line-progress.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/line-progress/src/instance.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/line-progress.scss`\n\n## Evidence Status\n\n- Demo confirmed:\n  - `src/demo-pages/component/progress/index.vue`\n- Source paths mapped:\n  - `components/line-progress/src/line-progress.vue`\n  - `components/line-progress/src/line-progress.ts`\n- Still verify in source:\n  - exact percent range assumptions\n  - animation behavior and any additional label slots\n"
