    "uri": "tuniao://tnui/components/loading",
    "name": "loading",
    "description": "tn-loading Loading",
    "mimeType": "text/markdown",
    "content": "# tn-loading Loading\n\n---\ncategory: display\ntitle: Loading / 加载指示器\ncomponent-dir: loading\nprimary-tags:\n  - tn-loading\nrelated-tags: []\nstatus: stable\nsource-dir: node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/loading\nstyle-source:\n  - node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/loading.scss\ndemo-pages:\n  - src/demo-pages/component/loading/index.vue\n---\n\n## Component Role\n\n`tn-loading` is a reusable loading indicator for inline loading, overlay bodies,\nand small feedback areas that need motion.\n\n## Best Fit Scenarios\n\n- inline loading indicators inside cards or sections\n- custom popup, modal, or overlay bodies that need a spinner\n- refresh or fetch states where a lightweight animation is enough\n- status displays that should avoid full-page skeletons\n\n## Avoid Using It For\n\n- empty states after loading has completed\n- list pagination states that are better expressed by `loadmore`\n- complex progress reporting that needs percentages or steps\n\n## Recommended Repo Usage\n\n```vue\n<tn-loading show animation />\n```\n\n## Key Capabilities\n\n### Indicator Variants\n\n- default circular style\n- `flower`\n- `semicircle`\n\n### Visual Controls\n\n- `type` theme colors such as `primary`, `success`, `warning`, `danger`, and\n  `info`\n- custom `color`\n- size presets and custom numeric size\n- animation timing controls such as `duration` and `time-function`\n\n## Boundary With Similar Components\n\n- use `loading` for a pure animated loading sign\n- use `loadmore` for list-bottom load states with explicit text such as\n  “loading” or “no more”\n- use `empty` when the request has ended and there is no content to show\n\n## AI Usage Notes\n\n- prefer `loading` when you only need a spinner-like affordance\n- pick the mode based on page tone; default is usually safest\n- keep the loading indicator near the area that is actually waiting\n- confirm whether `show` is mandatory or optional in source before creating a\n  wrapper component\n\n## Related Demos\n\n- `src/demo-pages/component/loading/index.vue`\n\n## Drill-Down Paths\n\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/loading/src/loading.vue`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/loading/src/loading.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/loading/src/instance.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/loading.scss`\n\n## Evidence Status\n\n- Demo confirmed:\n  - `src/demo-pages/component/loading/index.vue`\n- Source paths mapped:\n  - `components/loading/src/loading.vue`\n  - `components/loading/src/loading.ts`\n- Still verify in source:\n  - exact show/hide control semantics\n  - whether other animation modes or expose methods exist\n"
