    "uri": "tuniao://tnui/components/tag",
    "name": "tag",
    "description": "tn-tag Tag",
    "mimeType": "text/markdown",
    "content": "# tn-tag Tag\n\n---\ncategory: display\ntitle: Tag / 标签\ncomponent-dir: tag\nprimary-tags:\n  - tn-tag\nrelated-tags: []\nstatus: stable\nsource-dir: node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/tag\nstyle-source:\n  - node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/tag.scss\ndemo-pages: []\n---\n\n## Component Role\n\n`tn-tag` is a lightweight semantic chip for labeling status, category, or small\npieces of metadata.\n\n## Best Fit Scenarios\n\n- status labels such as “进行中” or “已完成”\n- category chips on cards and list rows\n- compact metadata grouping\n- visual filtering summaries\n\n## Avoid Using It For\n\n- unread counts that belong to `badge`\n- large selectable segmented controls\n- long descriptions or paragraph-like metadata blocks\n\n## Recommended Repo Usage\n\n```vue\n<tn-tag type=\"primary\">推荐</tn-tag>\n```\n\nPrefer tags for short semantic labels instead of hand-built rounded text pills.\n\n## Key Capabilities\n\n### Likely Usage Surface\n\n- themed color or type variants\n- size and shape styling\n- short slot text content\n- optional plain or filled visual modes\n\n### Integration Pattern\n\n- works well beside titles, list cells, or cards\n- can be repeated as lightweight metadata chips\n\n## Boundary With Similar Components\n\n- use `tag` for semantic labels with short text\n- use `badge` for counts, dots, and attached corner markers\n- use `title` when the text is a section heading rather than metadata\n\n## AI Usage Notes\n\n- keep tag text short and scannable\n- use tags to categorize, not to carry full explanations\n- because this repo currently has no dedicated tag demo page, confirm exact prop\n  names and variants from source before relying on advanced styling\n- if pages need selectable tags, verify whether the component itself supports\n  active state or whether page state must be layered on top\n\n## Related Demos\n\n- No dedicated `tn-tag` demo page was found in `src/demo-pages/`\n\n## Drill-Down Paths\n\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/tag/src/tag.vue`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/tag/src/tag.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/tag/src/instance.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/tag.scss`\n\n## Evidence Status\n\n- Demo confirmed:\n  - no dedicated repo demo page found\n- Source paths mapped:\n  - `components/tag/src/tag.vue`\n  - `components/tag/src/tag.ts`\n- Still verify in source:\n  - exact supported `type`, `shape`, and size props\n  - whether closeable or selectable behavior exists\n"
