    "uri": "tuniao://tnui/components/week-calendar",
    "name": "week-calendar",
    "description": "tn-week-calendar Week Calendar",
    "mimeType": "text/markdown",
    "content": "# tn-week-calendar Week Calendar\n\n---\ncategory: form\ntitle: Week Calendar / 周历\ncomponent-dir: week-calendar\nprimary-tags:\n  - tn-week-calendar\nrelated-tags: []\nstatus: stable\nsource-dir: node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/week-calendar\nstyle-source:\n  - node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/week-calendar.scss\ndemo-pages:\n  - src/demo-pages/component/week-calendar/index.vue\n---\n\n## Component Role\n\n`tn-week-calendar` is a compact calendar strip for choosing dates within a\ngiven month view.\n\n## Best Fit Scenarios\n\n- weekly or short-window date selection\n- attendance, sign-in, or compact schedule displays\n- pages where a full month calendar would be visually heavy\n- showing per-day annotations in a small footprint\n\n## Avoid Using It For\n\n- large range selection across months\n- full embedded monthly calendar interactions\n- time-of-day input\n\n## Recommended Repo Usage\n\n```vue\n<tn-week-calendar v-model=\"selectedDate\" />\n```\n\n## Key Capabilities\n\n### Date Controls\n\n- `v-model` for the selected date value\n- explicit `year` and `month`\n- `min-date`\n- `max-date`\n\n### Presentation And Data\n\n- `active-bg-color`\n- `custom-data` for per-day descriptions shown below specific dates\n\n## Boundary With Similar Components\n\n- use `week-calendar` for compact date strips and day-level annotations\n- use `calendar` when users need a fuller month-grid interaction\n- use `date-time-picker` when a popup wheel selector is a better fit\n\n## AI Usage Notes\n\n- confirm what the bound value represents before storing it; the demo uses\n  numeric day values\n- use `custom-data` when each date needs a short status marker\n- pin year and month explicitly when the page context already determines them\n- verify cross-month navigation behavior and emitted events from source before\n  building schedule logic around it\n\n## Related Demos\n\n- `src/demo-pages/component/week-calendar/index.vue`\n\n## Drill-Down Paths\n\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/week-calendar/src/week-calendar.vue`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/week-calendar/src/week-calendar.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/week-calendar/src/types.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/components/week-calendar/src/instance.ts`\n- `node_modules/@tuniao/tnui-vue3-uniapp/theme-chalk/src/week-calendar.scss`\n\n## Evidence Status\n\n- Demo confirmed:\n  - `src/demo-pages/component/week-calendar/index.vue`\n- Source paths mapped:\n  - `components/week-calendar/src/week-calendar.vue`\n  - `components/week-calendar/src/week-calendar.ts`\n  - `components/week-calendar/src/types.ts`\n- Still verify in source:\n  - whether the selected value is strictly a day number or a richer date model\n  - month switching or gesture support beyond the demo\n"
